@Plastic Jones

Force produces acceleration, a change in motion. With no force, an object's motion will not change. 

This is a very, very common misconception, but a fascinating one. (I can recommend some fun instructional materials that address it.)

@Plastic Jones
Inertia - A property of matter by which it continues in its existing state of rest or uniform motion in a straight line, unless that state is changed by an external force.
